Package: cumba
Type: Package
Title: Carbon Use Model for Yield and Brix Assessment in Processing Tomato
Version: 0.0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Federica", "Carucci",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Simone", "Bregaglio",
           email = "simone.bregaglio@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: A daily time-step crop model for processing tomato that simulates
    thermal time, phenology, root growth, a three-layer soil-water balance,
    carbon accumulation modulated by heat, cold and water stress, and predicts
    fresh-fruit yield and Brix at harvest. Two top-level entry points are
    provided: 'cumba_experiment()' replays observed irrigation schedules
    (used for calibration), and 'cumba_scenario()' runs the model in
    deficit-irrigation scenario mode, with irrigation triggered automatically
    on phase-specific water-stress thresholds.
